intro: Taenais australasiae, commonly known as the Australian taeniopsis, is a flowering plant native to Australia. It belongs to the family Myrtaceae, which includes eucalyptus and tea trees. The plant is characterized by its small, clustered white flowers and leathery, elliptical leaves. It typically grows in dry, sandy soils and is often found in coastal regions. Taenais australasiae is well adapted to the harsh conditions of its native habitat, showcasing resilience to drought and salt spray.
